{{Infobox musical artist | name = 4th Pyramid | background = non_performing_personnel | image = | birth_name = Adam Farag | alias = Fourth, Pyramid | origin = [[Toronto|Toronto, Ontario]], Canada | occupation = Rapper, songwriter, producer, DJ | years_active = <!-- 2003–present --> | label = [[Definitive Jux]], [[Universal Music Group]], [[Scion A/V]] | associated_acts = [[Jazz Cartier]], [[El-P]], [[Wu-Tang Clan]], [[Nice & Smooth|Greg Nice]], [[Cannibal Ox]], [[Grandtheft]], [[MF Doom]] | website = [http://www.4thpyramid.com 4thpyramid.com] }}
'''Adam Farag''', professionally known as '''4th Pyramid''', is a [[hip hop]] recording artist, producer, songwriter and [[disc jockey|DJ]] from [[Toronto, Ontario]] of [[Egypt]]ian descent.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.villagevoice.com/2012/03/20/qa-4th-pyramid-on-touring-with-too-hort-and-wu-tang-hooking-up-with-cosmo-baker-and-the-makings-of-a-good-hypeman/|title=Q&A: 4th Pyramid On Touring With Too $hort And Wu-Tang, Hooking Up With Cosmo Baker, And The Makings Of A Good Hypeman - Village Voice|website=villagevoice.com|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref> He is currently the official DJ for Toronto rapper and Juno-award winner,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://junoawards.ca/nomination/rap-recording-of-the-year-jazz-cartier/|title=RAP RECORDING OF THE YEAR - Jazz Cartier - The JUNO Awards|website=junoawards.ca|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref> [[Jazz Cartier]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ca.complex.com/music/2017/05/jazz-cartier-red-bull-sound-select-tour|title=Here's an Exclusive Look at Jazz Cartier's Red Bull Sound Select Tour|website=Complex CA|language=en|access-date=2017-07-27}}</ref>
== Career == === Beginnings === Pyramid entered the hip hop scene with the release of his self-produced debut album, ''The Light is But a Shade of the Darkness','' an instrumental full-length.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://exclaim.ca/music/article/4th_pyramid-light_is_but_shade_of|title=4th Pyramid The Light Is But The Shade Of The Darkness|website=exclaim.ca|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref> [[Chuck D]] of [[Public Enemy (band)|Public Enemy]] handpicked 4th Pyramid's 'Wallabee Strut' as one of the best 100 MP3s of 2000.''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newcanadianmusic.ca/artists/4/4th-pyramid|title=4Th Pyramid|website=New Canadian Music|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref> ''He was signed to rap label [[Definitive Jux]], owned by [[El-P]] ([[Run the Jewels]]), and appeared on the album [[Definitive Jux Presents Vol. III|Definitive Jux Presents III]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Various-Definitive-Jux-Presents-III/release/245086|title=Various - Definitive Jux Presents III|website=Discogs|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref> During this time, he also collaborated with label mates including [[Cannibal Ox]] and [[Camu Tao]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/1873-definitive-jux-presents-iii/|title=Various Artists: Definitive Jux Presents III Album Review - Pitchfork|website=pitchfork.com|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref>
=== Rap === 4th Pyramid released his debut solo rap album ''The Pyramid Scheme'' in 2012<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://exclaim.ca/music/article/4th_pyramid-pyramid_scheme|title=4th Pyramid The Pyramid Scheme|access-date=2017-07-27|language=en}}</ref> after signing a deal with [[Universal Music Canada]]. The album included the single "''It's So Hot''" featuring [[Greg Nice]] of [[Nice and Smooth]] in 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Sheen-Bros-4th-Pyramid-Cosmo-Baker-Its-So-Hot-EP/release/3613521|title=Sheen Bros - 4th Pyramid & Cosmo Baker - It's So Hot EP|website=Discogs|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref> The track was featured in the film [[21 and Over (film)|21 and Over]] and also appeared on the film's soundtrack.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://exclaim.ca/music/article/4th_pyramid|title=4th Pyramid|website=exclaim.ca|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref> The album also included collaborations with [[Saukrates]], Marco Polo<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://nowtoronto.com/music/4th-pyramids-feel-it-in-my-bones/|title=4th Pyramid's Feel It In My Bones|date=2012-06-20|work=NOW Magazine|access-date=2017-07-28|language=en-us}}</ref> & more. In 2013, he released the EP ''The Sky Belongs To The Stars'' which included the single "Friday Nights" produced by [[Grandtheft]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://exclaim.ca/music/article/4th_pyramid-sky_belongs_to_stars|title=4th Pyramid The Sky Belongs To The Stars|access-date=2017-07-27|language=en}}</ref> He has toured with [[Wu-Tang Clan]], [[ASAP Rocky]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hiphopcanada.com/2013/02/torontos-4th-pyramid-to-share-stage-with-asap-rocky-more-in-brooklyn-news/|title=Toronto's 4th Pyramid To Share Stage With A$AP Rocky & More In Brooklyn [News]|date=2013-02-01|work=HipHopCanada.com|access-date=2017-07-28}}</ref> [[De La Soul]], [[Elzhi]], [[The Pharcyde]] and others.
=== Production === 4th has produced and engineered tracks for the [[The Black Eyed Peas|Black Eyed Peas]], members of [[Wu-Tang Clan]], [[Pete Rock]] and others.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/artist/622798-Adam-Farag|title=Adam Farag|website=Discogs|language=en|access-date=2017-07-27}}</ref>
=== DJ === 4th Pyramid formed the DJ group, ''Sheen Bros'' with Philadelphia DJ, [[Cosmo Baker]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.itstherub.com/sheen-brothers-cosmo-baker-4th-pyramid-scumbag-funk-vol-2/|title=The Rub » Sheen Brothers (Cosmo Baker + 4th Pyramid): Scumbag Funk Vol. 2|website=www.itstherub.com|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref> and they released several mixtapes together<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://yourfriendshouse.com/uncategorised/sheen-bros-its-so-hot-ep/amp/|title=Sheen Bros / Its So Hot EP|date=2011-08-04|work=Your Friend's House|access-date=2017-07-27|language=en}}</ref> and an EP through the [[Scion Audio/Visual|Scion/AV]] label. 4th Pyramid continues to DJ internationally and is currently the official DJ for [[Capitol Records]] recording artist, [[Jazz Cartier]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ca.complex.com/music/2017/05/jazz-cartier-red-bull-sound-select-tour|title=Here's an Exclusive Look at Jazz Cartier's Red Bull Sound Select Tour|website=Complex CA|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref> The two have toured Europe, North America and Canada including a tour with [[Post Malone]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hotnewhiphop.com/jazz-cartier-announces-secret-garden-tour-news.30120.html?|title=Jazz Cartier Announces "Secret Garden" Tour|website=hotnewhiphop.com|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref>
