{{Multiple issues| {{one source|date=May 2011}} {{notability|Biographies|date=May 2011}} }} {{Infobox saint | name = Aberoh and Atom (brothers) | image = | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | titles = Saints | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | venerated_in = Coptic Orthodox Church [[Roman Catholic Church]] | beatified_date = | beatified_place = | beatified_by = | canonized_date = | canonized_place = | canonized_by = | major_shrine = | feast_day = July 2 | attributes = | patronage = | issues = | suppressed_date = | suppressed_by = | quote = }}
'''Aberoh and Atom''' are [[martyr]]s of the [[Christian church]].
These brothers were citizens of [[Gamnudi]] in [[Egypt]]. They fled Gamnudi during a persecution for [[Pelusium]] (then Farama). They were arrested at [[Alexandria]] and tortured. After being dismissed by the prefect, they went next to Baramon, where they were [[decapitation|beheaded]]. Their [[relics]] were returned to Gamnudi. Their [[feast day]] is July 2 in the [[Coptic Orthodox Church of Alexandria|Coptic Church]].<ref>[http://www.catholic.org/saints/saint.php?saint_id=6065/ St. Aberoh (Aburom, Arianus)] Retrieved on 15 Feb 2018</ref>
