'''NASA Categories of Evidence''' comprise a matrix or scale denoting the sources of evidence provided in the [[Human Research Program]]'s various [[evidence]] reports, and thus potentially their [[probative]] value and [[efficacy]].<ref>[http://humanresearchroadmap.nasa.gov/Evidence/ NASA Categories of Evidence]</ref> Authors in the Program were urged to label their evidence according to whether it was based on [[controlled experiment]]s, [[observation]], or [[expert opinion]].
{| class="wikitable" <div style="text-align: center;"> !scope="col" width="150"|Broad "Experimental" Design Type !scope="col" width="300"|Silagy & Haines Lelvels of Evidence<ref>{{cite book|last=Silagy|first=C|title=Evidence Based Practice in Primary Care |edition=2nd |date=2001|publisher=BMJ Books|location=London|url=http://die-serie.com/Books/Evidence_Based_Practice_in_Primary_Care.pdf|author2=Haines, A}}</ref> !scope="col" width="300"|Nasa Categories of Evidence |- |rowspan="4" | Controlled |Ia - [[Meta-analysis]] of [[Randomized trial|randomized trials]] |rowspan="2" | I - At least one randomized, [[controlled trial]] |- |Ib - At least one randomized [[Clinical trial|trial]] |- |IIa - At least one controlled study [[non-random|without randomization]] |rowspan="2" | II - At least one controlled study without randomization, including [[Cohort study|cohort]], [[Case–control study|case-control]], or [[Human subject research|subject]] operating as own [[Control (science)|control]]. |- |IIb - At least one other [[Quasi-experiment|quasi-experimental]] [[experiment|study]] |- |Observational |III - [[Non-experimental]] descriptive studies, e.g. comparative [[correlation]] or [[Case study|case studies]]. |III - Non-experimental observations or comparative, correlation, and case or [[Case series|case-series]] studies. |- |[[Opinion]] |IV - Expert committee reports or opinions or clinical experiences of respected authorities. |IV - Expert committee reports or opinions of respected authorities based on clinical experiences, [[bench research]], or "[[first principle]]s". |- |}
